%html{ lang: "en" }
  %head
    %meta{ charset: "utf-8" }
    %link{ rel: 'stylesheet', href: 'stylesheets/normalize.css' }
    %link{ rel: 'stylesheet', href: 'stylesheets/main.css' }
    %link{ rel: 'stylesheet', type: 'text/css', href: "https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lora:400,700"}
    %link{ rel: 'stylesheet', type: 'text/css', href: "https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Source+Sans+Pro:400,700"}
    %title Benjamin Miller | Software Engineer
  %body
    %header
      %div.full-width
        %div.half-width
          %h1 Benjamin Miller
        %div.half-width
          %nav
            %ul
              %li
                %a{ href: "#about" }About
              %li
                %a{ href: "#work" }Work
              %li
                %a{ href: "#contact" }Contact
        %h2
          %span Hi,
          %br
          I'm a software engineer.
    %main
      %section#about
        %div.full-width
          %h2 About Me
          %div.half-width
            %p
              I am a father of two boys and software engineer living in the New   |
              York City area. I'm a proud graduate of Western Carolina University |
              who's been in the software industry since 2013. Beginning with      |
              .NET development, I quickly jumped to J2EE on Spring and            |
              Struts, Python and Perl, and SOA development at Red Hat.            |
          %div.half-width
            %p
              I eventually branched into Ruby on Rails and JavaScript, as well as |
              myriad other web technologies and frameworks. I currently work on   |
              full-stack anomaly detection in big data at Cigna, working in a JS  |
              stack, AWS, and Golang.
          %div.half-width
            %p
              In my spare time, I work to encourage and support new developers on   |
              their journey to break into our industry. I love learning new things, |
              learning new ways to think, and getting new perspectives on any and   |
              all subjects!
      %section#work
        %div.full-width
          %div.third-width
            %img{ src: 'img/icon-html.png', alt: 'Console Icon'}
            %h3 General Skills and Tools
            %p
              Linux preferred, Mac OSX tolerated; Ruby, Elixir, |
              JavaScript, Java, GoLang, Python, Perl, C; Zsh and all *nix |
              tools, Atom, Vim, IntelliJ
          %div.third-width
            %img{ src: 'img/icon-css.png', alt: 'Web Page Icon' }
            %h3 Speciality Areas
            %p
              Full-Stack Web Engineering, SOA/Microservice Architecture, API   |
              Design, Middleware
          %div.third-width
            %img{ src: 'img/icon-pencil.png', alt: 'Pencil Icon' }
            %h3 Frameworks and Soft Skills
            %p
              Ruby on Rails, React/NodeJS, Angular, SQL/NoSQL databases, |
              Spring, Struts, and facilitating healthy, productive communication.
      %footer#contact
        %div.full-width
          %div.half-width
            %a{ href: 'mailto:bmiller@millerb.com' }
              %img#contact-img{ src: 'img/contact.jpg', alt: 'Contact' }
          %div.half-width
            %h2 Want to collaborate?
            %h3#email-header Let's meet for a cup of coffee.
            %a{ href: 'mailto:bmiller@millerb.com'}
              %img#envelope{ src: 'img/icon-envelope.png', alt: 'Envelope Icon' }
              bmiller [@] millerb.com
            %h3#socialmedia-header
              Or, find me at any of this exciting array of internet websites:
            %ul
              %li
                %a{ href: 'https://www.linkedin.com/in/benjamin-miller-9ba9b9174' }
                  %img{ src: 'img/icon-linkedin.png', alt: 'LinkedIn Icon' }
              %li
                %a{ href: 'https://twitter.com/BenjaminCodes' }
                  %img{ src: 'img/icon-twitter.png', alt: 'Twitter Icon' }
              %li
